headline: New Debit Cards Have an Unexpected Feature: Rewards
summary: Debit cards are getting the credit-card treatment.  This year  Southwest Airlines United Airlines  and  Wyndham Hotels & Resorts  launched debit cards that let customers earn points and miles.  Venmo’s debit card now offers 5% cash back at certain merchants, and Klarna added a premium debit tier that comes with a rose-gold card and access to airport lounges for about $540 a year.
